The recent claim of a $100 b asset profile for the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints is thus far unsubstantiated, with the only confirmation coming from a former employee of the Church with no documentation. The $32 b estimate is not only more conservative (wikipedia is not in the business of sensationalism), but has at least some supporting documentation and more than one single person making the claim.
